00:16:09,403 --> 00:16:12,053
So the important thing
for the American people
to know

250
00:16:12,122 --> 00:16:13,715
is that
they're safe,

251
00:16:13,786 --> 00:16:16,273
that they can
go on about
their daily lives,

252
00:16:16,346 --> 00:16:18,233
This is unbelievable.

253
00:16:19,961 --> 00:16:21,422
James,

254
00:16:21,497 --> 00:16:25,806
I know you went
through a terrible
ordeal in Alaska.

255
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:27,341
But you're
home now.

256
00:16:27,416 --> 00:16:31,093
Okay? So let someone
else do the worrying
for a change.

257
00:16:31,159 --> 00:16:33,973
Enjoy being
with your family.

258
00:16:36,566 --> 00:16:37,973
You're right.

259
00:16:38,038 --> 00:16:39,499
You're right
as usual.

260
00:16:39,574 --> 00:16:40,784
Mm-hm.

261
00:16:44,085 --> 00:16:46,125
The United States
of America
[static]

262
00:16:46,197 --> 00:16:49,971
stands ready
to offer assistance all
available citizens necessary.

263
00:16:50,036 --> 00:16:52,305
[loud piercing noise]

264
00:16:52,372 --> 00:16:54,706
What is that
terrible sound?

265
00:16:58,131 --> 00:17:00,552
[static, shrill sound]

266
00:17:00,626 --> 00:17:04,106
[loud humming
in crescendo]

267
00:17:08,145 --> 00:17:10,599
[loud thuds]

268
00:17:13,137 --> 00:17:13,998
An earthquake?

269
00:17:14,064 --> 00:17:15,590
Quick, take cover!

270
00:17:28,397 --> 00:17:29,509
Shane, you okay?

271
00:17:29,581 --> 00:17:32,777
[door opens]

272
00:17:33,868 --> 00:17:35,756
Yeah.

273
00:17:49,130 --> 00:17:50,374
What?

274
00:18:04,040 --> 00:18:05,894
What?

275
00:18:05,959 --> 00:18:08,064
(James, over phone)
What do you mean
it's been classified?

276
00:18:08,135 --> 00:18:09,411
Just what I said.

277
00:18:09,478 --> 00:18:10,940
All the data we
collected in Alaska

278
00:18:11,014 --> 00:18:13,502
and uploaded
to Government
has been classified.

279
00:18:13,574 --> 00:18:16,355
And neither you nor
I have the clearance
to access it.

280
00:18:16,422 --> 00:18:18,243
In fact, we shouldn't
even be talking about
this right now.

281
00:18:18,309 --> 00:18:20,064
The whole dept's
under a gag order.

282
00:18:20,132 --> 00:18:21,409
That tremor
we just had

283
00:18:21,477 --> 00:18:23,418
was preceded
by some kind of
EM disturbance

284
00:18:23,492 --> 00:18:25,467
which could mean
that there's been
serious damage

285
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:26,783
to the
magnetic field.

286
00:18:26,851 --> 00:18:29,534
Yeah. I recorded
an EM spike earlier

287
00:18:29,603 --> 00:18:31,010
but I didn't know
what caused it.

288
00:18:31,075 --> 00:18:34,424
We need the
comet data. Who
classified it?

289
00:18:34,498 --> 00:18:36,473
The Administration.

290
00:18:36,546 --> 00:18:40,701
Great. Not even a
comet hit is immune
to political spin.

291
00:18:40,769 --> 00:18:42,908
Maybe there really
was some damage
to the field

292
00:18:42,977 --> 00:18:46,205
and they don't want
to disclose it to
the public.

293
00:18:46,272 --> 00:18:48,061
We need
to find out.

294
00:18:48,128 --> 00:18:49,535
(female recorded voice)
You've reached the office

295
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,258
of the President's
Science Adviser.

296
00:18:51,328 --> 00:18:53,237
Due to
extenuating circumstances,

297
00:18:53,312 --> 00:18:55,253
this office will not
be taking phone calls

298
00:18:55,327 --> 00:18:57,334
until further notice.
[beep]

299
00:18:59,742 --> 00:19:01,564
[deep sigh]

300
00:19:16,092 --> 00:19:18,164
[buzzing]

301
00:19:32,697 --> 00:19:34,322
What are you
doing up on
the roof?

302
00:19:34,392 --> 00:19:36,431
T racking the sun.

303
00:19:36,504 --> 00:19:39,286
And why would you
be tracking
the sun?

304
00:19:39,351 --> 00:19:41,772
It's not where
it's supposed
to be.

305
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,538
Why would
you say that?

306
00:19:43,607 --> 00:19:46,192
Yesterday, the
sun set behind
Eagle Peak.

307
00:19:46,262 --> 00:19:49,163
What do you mean?
It's never set
behind the Peak.

308
00:19:51,477 --> 00:19:52,492
Exactly.

309
00:19:56,788 --> 00:20:00,846
[phone rings]

310
00:20:00,915 --> 00:20:02,671
Hello?

311
00:20:02,739 --> 00:20:04,746
(girl's voice)
Hey! Is
this Shane?

312
00:20:04,819 --> 00:20:05,767
Yeah, who's this?

313
00:20:05,843 --> 00:20:07,370
Hi, it's Zoe.

314
00:20:07,442 --> 00:20:10,192
I was just calling to
tell Miss Penny the
pastries are ready.

315
00:20:10,258 --> 00:20:11,850
Pastries?

316
00:20:11,921 --> 00:20:13,928
We're donating
them for the school's
disaster fund drive.

317
00:20:14,001 --> 00:20:15,724
So she can
pick them up
whenever she wants.

318
00:20:15,793 --> 00:20:18,095
Okay, I'll let
her know.

319
00:20:18,161 --> 00:20:19,687
Okay.
Bye.

320
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:20,709
Bye.

321
00:20:22,768 --> 00:20:24,328
Hi.

322
00:20:24,399 --> 00:20:25,992
Zoe just called.

323
00:20:26,064 --> 00:20:28,235
The pastries for
the fund drive
are ready.

324
00:20:28,303 --> 00:20:29,928
Want me to go pick
them up for you?

325
00:20:29,999 --> 00:20:32,813
That would be
great, Shane.
Thank you.

326
00:20:44,780 --> 00:20:46,024
Can I help you?

327
00:20:47,756 --> 00:20:49,763
Oh.
Hi.

328
00:20:50,635 --> 00:20:52,162
How's it going?

329
00:20:52,235 --> 00:20:55,201
Good. You're here
to pick up the stuff
for your mom, right?

330
00:20:55,274 --> 00:20:56,768
She's not my mom.

331
00:20:56,842 --> 00:20:59,209
Okay. Step-mom.

332
00:20:59,274 --> 00:21:01,761
Hey. You have
my sympathy.

333
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:04,320
I'd die if my dad
picked one of
my teachers.

334
00:21:04,393 --> 00:21:06,978
[cell rings]

335
00:21:07,048 --> 00:21:09,153
Hello?
Hey!

336
00:21:21,446 --> 00:21:22,460
My God.

337
00:21:22,534 --> 00:21:24,094
What is it?

338
00:21:24,165 --> 00:21:27,776
The sun's 10 degrees
off where it should
be this time of year.

339
00:21:27,845 --> 00:21:30,463
How can that be?

340
00:21:37,124 --> 00:21:40,352
Okay. In like
an hour?

341
00:21:40,419 --> 00:21:43,615
You still meeting
Kevin at the
park today?

342
00:21:43,682 --> 00:21:45,144
Uh, yeah.

343
00:21:46,306 --> 00:21:47,483
Yeah, okay.

344
00:21:47,553 --> 00:21:49,375
Alright, okay.
Bye.

345
00:21:52,608 --> 00:21:53,590
Here it is.

346
00:21:53,664 --> 00:21:54,744
Thanks.

347
00:21:54,817 --> 00:21:56,507
I'll be at
the park
with Kevin.

348
00:21:56,576 --> 00:21:57,525
Oh, yeah?

349
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:58,582
Yeah.

350
00:21:58,656 --> 00:21:59,801
I'll see
you there.

351
00:21:59,872 --> 00:22:00,820
Cool.

352
00:22:12,030 --> 00:22:13,491
[car door closes]

353
00:22:15,901 --> 00:22:16,849
Hey, James!

354
00:22:16,925 --> 00:22:18,451
Hey, Lou!

355
00:22:18,524 --> 00:22:21,109
I haven't had a chance
to talk to you since
the interview.

356
00:22:21,180 --> 00:22:25,271
So, what's
this great story
you've got for me?

357
00:22:25,339 --> 00:22:26,932
You remember how
we used to come
out here

358
00:22:27,003 --> 00:22:28,214
and watch all
those sunsets?

359
00:22:28,283 --> 00:22:29,744
Maybe that's what
you came out
here for.

360
00:22:29,819 --> 00:22:31,793
I was out here
for the babes
and the booze.

361
00:22:31,866 --> 00:22:35,542
Do you remember how this
sundial was always right
on the money?

362
00:22:35,609 --> 00:22:37,103
Yeah, I remember.

363
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:47,221
[loud music from car]

364
00:22:58,294 --> 00:23:02,221
[motor revs]

365
00:23:17,522 --> 00:23:18,634
Hey, Shane.

366
00:23:18,706 --> 00:23:20,429
Hey, Zoe.

367
00:23:20,498 --> 00:23:21,840
So what am l?
Chopped liver?

368
00:23:23,474 --> 00:23:25,994
So, Shane buddy, l
got a little problem
because of you.

369
00:23:26,065 --> 00:23:27,755
You see this car?

370
00:23:27,825 --> 00:23:31,719
My dad's making me sell it
to pay for the stupid
telescope you broke.

371
00:23:31,792 --> 00:23:32,740
We broke it.

372
00:23:32,816 --> 00:23:34,725
Whatever. The
point is,

373
00:23:34,799 --> 00:23:36,708
I think we
can settle this
little problem.

374
00:23:36,783 --> 00:23:38,473
How is that?

375
00:23:38,543 --> 00:23:40,549
Drag race.
You and me.

376
00:23:40,622 --> 00:23:44,812
You win, I'll pay the
4000 we owe for
the telescope.

377
00:23:44,878 --> 00:23:47,692
I win,
you pay.

378
00:23:49,389 --> 00:23:50,698
Come on, what
do you think?

379
00:23:50,764 --> 00:23:52,837
Not afraid of getting
your ass whupped,
are ya?

380
00:23:54,412 --> 00:23:55,873
You wouldn't win.

381
00:23:55,948 --> 00:23:59,046
Ouch. You
hear that?

382
00:23:59,115 --> 00:24:01,351
Greaser-boy thinks
he can beat me.

383
00:24:02,699 --> 00:24:04,422
Let's do it.

384
00:24:07,114 --> 00:24:09,416
Dr. Mayfield
says his suspicion
was first aroused

385
00:24:09,482 --> 00:24:11,848
when he noticed
the sun setting
behind Eagle Peak.

386
00:24:11,913 --> 00:24:14,979
Now, I can tell you
from my own experience
as I was growing up here,

387
00:24:15,049 --> 00:24:17,285
the sun has never
set behind Eagle
Peak before.

388
00:24:17,352 --> 00:24:19,043
And then there's our
trusty sundial here

389
00:24:19,112 --> 00:24:24,708
which has never
been wrong.

390
00:24:24,775 --> 00:24:26,084
Until today.

391
00:24:26,151 --> 00:24:30,176
[motors rev loudly]

392
00:24:46,276 --> 00:24:50,269
[piercing sound
from radio]

393
00:24:55,170 --> 00:24:56,185
Ready, guys?

394
00:24:59,073 --> 00:25:00,055
Get set--

395
00:25:18,366 --> 00:25:19,413
[shout]

396
00:25:28,157 --> 00:25:29,979
Shane! Get
out, Shane!

397
00:25:31,195 --> 00:25:32,089
Shane!

398
00:25:36,731 --> 00:25:38,073
Shane! Get out!

399
00:25:41,978 --> 00:25:43,287
Oh, my God.

400
00:25:56,088 --> 00:25:57,036
You okay?

401
00:25:57,111 --> 00:25:58,802
Are you alright?

402
00:25:58,872 --> 00:26:01,075
[heavy breathing]

403
00:26:01,143 --> 00:26:03,510
What happened?
What just happened?

404
00:26:03,574 --> 00:26:06,890
Poor Kevin.
Oh, my God.

405
00:26:15,156 --> 00:26:17,011
I can't
get reception.
What about you?

406
00:26:17,076 --> 00:26:18,320
Nothing.

407
00:26:20,436 --> 00:26:21,996
What is that?

408
00:26:22,067 --> 00:26:24,936
[dull roar]

409
00:26:26,322 --> 00:26:28,078
It looks like
an aurora.

410
00:26:28,146 --> 00:26:30,513
Here? I thought
those things only
happened up north

411
00:26:30,578 --> 00:26:31,952
in places
like Alaska.

412
00:26:35,121 --> 00:26:36,943
Something bad's happening.

413
00:26:39,504 --> 00:26:40,911
Dr. Mayfield,
what exactly
is the problem

414
00:26:41,424 --> 00:26:43,758
with an axis
tilt changing
ten degrees?

415
00:26:43,824 --> 00:26:47,751
I mean, so
what if the sun
sets 10 minutes later?

416
00:26:47,823 --> 00:26:49,449
A shifted axis tilt

417
00:26:49,519 --> 00:26:51,558
means the
Earth's axis
of rotation

418
00:26:51,630 --> 00:26:53,997
is out of alignment
with its magnetic poles.

419
00:26:54,062 --> 00:26:57,574
This could have serious
consequences for the
Earth's magnetic field.

420
00:26:57,645 --> 00:26:59,881
Seismic activity,
electromagnetic interference

421
00:26:59,949 --> 00:27:02,404
with communications
that we've
been experiencing,

422
00:27:02,477 --> 00:27:05,859
This could
all be just
the beginning.

423
00:27:05,932 --> 00:27:08,266
The beginning
of what?

424
00:27:08,332 --> 00:27:11,048
A catastrophic
pole reversal.

425
00:27:12,619 --> 00:27:14,626
You mean like
what happened
a million years ago

426
00:27:14,699 --> 00:27:17,633
when the north
and south poles
changed places?

427
00:27:17,706 --> 00:27:19,200
That's right.

428
00:27:20,329 --> 00:27:21,278
Back to you.

429
00:27:23,017 --> 00:27:26,464
(James)
Yeah! Yeah!
Alright already!

430
00:27:28,872 --> 00:27:31,327
James, buddy,
we are famous.

431
00:27:31,400 --> 00:27:32,643
What are you
talking about?

432
00:27:32,711 --> 00:27:34,598
[guffaws]

433
00:27:34,663 --> 00:27:35,873
You don't know?

434
00:27:35,943 --> 00:27:37,797
Know what?

435
00:27:39,494 --> 00:27:41,217
Your story
caught fire.

436
00:27:41,286 --> 00:27:43,969
My report got
picked up by all
the big networks.

437
00:27:44,038 --> 00:27:45,564
Really?

438
00:27:45,637 --> 00:27:47,524
Yeah. There is some
weird crap going on
all over this country

439
00:27:47,589 --> 00:27:49,083
that the government
does not want to
talk about

440
00:27:49,156 --> 00:27:51,327
but your theory
makes more sense
than these--

441
00:27:51,396 --> 00:27:54,592
alien invasion stories
so the networks
picked it up.

442
00:27:54,660 --> 00:27:58,271
Good. Maybe it'll force
the Administration to
come clean.

443
00:27:58,339 --> 00:28:01,022
Look, any more
earth-shattering
developments--

444
00:28:01,090 --> 00:28:02,846
I'm your man, right?

445
00:28:02,914 --> 00:28:03,929
See you, Lou.

446
00:28:04,002 --> 00:28:05,279
I'm your man, right?

447
00:28:05,346 --> 00:28:06,294
See you, Lou!

448
00:28:06,370 --> 00:28:07,614
I'm your man!

449
00:28:20,031 --> 00:28:21,438
Good morning, gentlemen.

450
00:28:21,503 --> 00:28:22,812
Good morning,
Mr. President.

451
00:28:22,879 --> 00:28:24,886
Good morning, Mr.
President. How
are you, sir?

452
00:28:24,959 --> 00:28:27,195
Who leaked the
axis tilt to
the press?

453
00:28:27,262 --> 00:28:29,116
A Dr. James
Mayfield, sir.

454
00:28:29,182 --> 00:28:31,865
Mayfield? That's your
son, isn't it, General?

455
00:28:31,934 --> 00:28:34,355
Yes, sir. Dr.
Mayfield is
my son.

456
00:28:34,429 --> 00:28:35,573
Then what the
heck's he doing

457
00:28:35,644 --> 00:28:36,986
leaking
classified information?

458
00:28:37,052 --> 00:28:39,190
I'm sorry, sir.
I'm not aware
of his activities.

459
00:28:39,260 --> 00:28:41,115
We haven't spoken
in nearly five years.

460
00:28:41,180 --> 00:28:42,968
You don't say.

461
00:28:43,035 --> 00:28:45,621
Maybe now would be
a good time for a
family reunion.

462
00:28:45,691 --> 00:28:48,657
Because if you can't
put a muzzle on him,
we will.

463
00:28:48,730 --> 00:28:51,185
What exactly was
his involvement
with this?

464
00:28:51,258 --> 00:28:54,257
Our Storm Hazard
Research Dept.
contracted Dr. Mayfield

465
00:28:54,329 --> 00:28:57,395
to monitor the
comet's effect on
the radiation belts.

466
00:28:57,465 --> 00:28:59,668
So wasn't this guy on
the same gag order
as everyone else?

467
00:28:59,736 --> 00:29:01,427
Yes, sir, and
his research
was classified,

468
00:29:01,497 --> 00:29:04,879
but to be honest, sir,
the data he updated

469
00:29:04,952 --> 00:29:06,675
couldn't have
revealed an
axis tilt

470
00:29:06,744 --> 00:29:09,231
as it was collected
prior to the
comet hit.

471
00:29:09,303 --> 00:29:11,245
Don't argue
semantics with
me, doctor.

472
00:29:11,319 --> 00:29:13,293
A gag order
is a gag order.

473
00:29:13,367 --> 00:29:16,366
I don't need 400 phone
calls coming into the
White House

474
00:29:16,438 --> 00:29:19,918
every hour about a pole
reversal that's not
going to happen.

475
00:29:19,989 --> 00:29:22,705
It's not going
to happen, right,
Dr. Elman?

476
00:29:22,772 --> 00:29:25,227
It's a preposterous
thought, Mr. President.

477
00:29:25,300 --> 00:29:27,471
The consensus
is that the
Earth's axis

478
00:29:27,540 --> 00:29:30,987
will slowly fall
back in place as
it rotates.

479
00:29:31,059 --> 00:29:32,466
Glad to hear it.

480
00:29:32,531 --> 00:29:35,181
However, this sort
of doomsday hysteria,

481
00:29:35,250 --> 00:29:38,184
is exactly why we need
to keep the public in
the dark right now.

482
00:29:38,258 --> 00:29:39,600
Your son--

483
00:29:39,666 --> 00:29:40,614
Sir?

484
00:29:40,690 --> 00:29:41,638
Is he smart?

485
00:29:41,713 --> 00:29:42,661
Yes, sir.

486
00:29:42,737 --> 00:29:43,784
How smart is he?

487
00:29:43,857 --> 00:29:44,969
Too smart for
his own good, sir.

488
00:29:45,041 --> 00:29:47,081
That's what it
sounds like.

489
00:29:47,153 --> 00:29:48,167
You better
bring him in.

490
00:29:48,240 --> 00:29:49,582
Yes, sir.

491
00:30:00,462 --> 00:30:01,738
James.

492
00:30:01,806 --> 00:30:05,035
It's really happening.
All the telltale signs.

493
00:30:05,101 --> 00:30:06,889
This is unprecedented.

494
00:30:06,957 --> 00:30:08,135
What is?

495
00:30:08,205 --> 00:30:10,823
The pole reversal.

496
00:30:10,893 --> 00:30:13,064
Shane didn't
come home
last night.

497
00:30:14,124 --> 00:30:15,553
Are you sure?

498
00:30:15,628 --> 00:30:17,515
Yeah, his car isn't here,
his bed hasn't been
slept in

499
00:30:17,579 --> 00:30:18,823
and I can't reach
him on his cell.

500
00:30:18,891 --> 00:30:20,167
He said he was going
to the park last night.

501
00:30:20,235 --> 00:30:21,926
Oh, my God. I just
heard on the radio

502
00:30:21,995 --> 00:30:24,744
the park was ripped
apart by a major
earthquake last night.

503
00:30:24,810 --> 00:30:25,758
Let's go!

504
00:30:37,448 --> 00:30:40,349
[sirens]

505
00:30:44,615 --> 00:30:46,207
What's going on?

