750
00:44:37,562 --> 00:44:39,471
don't have a clue.

751
00:44:42,393 --> 00:44:44,051
I have to
do this.

752
00:44:45,337 --> 00:44:46,384
For us.

753
00:44:50,456 --> 00:44:53,751
We're here, smack in
the middle of a mini
pole's magnetic center,

754
00:44:53,815 --> 00:44:55,603
the most
dangerous place
to be right now.

755
00:44:55,671 --> 00:44:57,231
Everywhere inside
this circle

756
00:44:57,302 --> 00:44:59,124
is gonna get
bombarded by
EM pulses

757
00:44:59,190 --> 00:45:01,165
and torn apart by
seismic disturbances.

758
00:45:01,238 --> 00:45:03,245
I want you guys
out of this circle

759
00:45:03,317 --> 00:45:05,456
as soon as possible.
Go to this town here,

760
00:45:05,526 --> 00:45:08,908
Little Brook
and wait for
me, okay?

761
00:45:08,981 --> 00:45:11,850
What are you
talking about, Dad?
You're coming, right?

762
00:45:13,652 --> 00:45:16,750
I can't.
I have to go
back to the base.

763
00:45:16,819 --> 00:45:19,950
I don't believe
it, you're
abandoning us?

764
00:45:20,019 --> 00:45:21,448
That sucks!

765
00:45:21,523 --> 00:45:24,272
Try to understand,
there is a global
crisis going on.

766
00:45:24,338 --> 00:45:25,931
You think
I don't
know that?

767
00:45:26,002 --> 00:45:28,336
I saw one of my classmates
crushed to death in
a car last night.

768
00:45:28,402 --> 00:45:30,573
I know.
I'm sorry.

769
00:45:30,641 --> 00:45:32,582
So you don't care
if the same thing
happens to us?

770
00:45:32,656 --> 00:45:34,827
Of course I do,
that's why I have
to fix this.

771
00:45:34,896 --> 00:45:35,845
We'll be okay.

772
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:36,935
Leave me alone.

773
00:45:39,664 --> 00:45:41,092
Shane, come on!

774
00:45:44,495 --> 00:45:47,244
When an EM wave hits,
turn the car off till
it passes.

775
00:45:49,038 --> 00:45:52,518
The electronics won't be
short-circuited as long as
the power's off.

776
00:45:52,589 --> 00:45:55,971
If the power's on,
you and the car
will fry.

777
00:45:56,045 --> 00:45:58,020
How long
will you be?

778
00:45:58,092 --> 00:46:00,231
A day.
Maybe two.

779
00:46:01,548 --> 00:46:02,955
Be careful.

780
00:46:03,019 --> 00:46:04,099
Yeah.

781
00:46:05,771 --> 00:46:06,753
You too.

782
00:46:20,456 --> 00:46:21,733
Shane?

783
00:46:21,801 --> 00:46:24,288
No! No!
No, no, no!

784
00:46:24,360 --> 00:46:25,920
Take those
earbuds off.

785
00:46:25,992 --> 00:46:27,650
Stay away
from electronics.

786
00:46:27,720 --> 00:46:30,175
You will
get electrocuted
if an EM wave hits.

787
00:46:31,591 --> 00:46:34,046
I'm serious.
It's dangerous.
Get rid of it.

788
00:46:38,214 --> 00:46:40,156
I'll see you soon.

789
00:46:40,229 --> 00:46:41,211
Hey--

790
00:46:43,301 --> 00:46:44,249
I love you.

791
00:46:52,995 --> 00:46:56,191
(male voice over radio)
All residents are
advised to remain tuned

792
00:46:56,259 --> 00:46:58,113
to this emergency
broadcast channel.

793
00:46:58,179 --> 00:47:00,796
Federal martial law
has been declared.

794
00:47:00,865 --> 00:47:03,483
Lindenville residents
are ordered to evacuate
their homes

795
00:47:03,553 --> 00:47:06,008
and take shelter
at Lindenville parish.

796
00:47:06,081 --> 00:47:10,074
Why are they telling
everyone to go
to the church?

797
00:47:10,145 --> 00:47:13,689
Didn't Dad say
it's dangerous
to stay in town?

798
00:47:19,935 --> 00:47:21,757
Oh, what's this?

799
00:47:31,453 --> 00:47:32,729
The road's closed.

800
00:47:32,796 --> 00:47:34,618
You're supposed to take
shelter in the parish.

801
00:47:34,684 --> 00:47:36,626
We're going
to Little Brook.

802
00:47:40,859 --> 00:47:44,633
Ma'am, we have orders
to divert everyone to
the Lindenville parish.

803
00:47:44,699 --> 00:47:46,902
That's ridiculous.
It's not even
safe there.

804
00:47:46,970 --> 00:47:49,042
Ma'am, please,
just back it up.

805
00:47:49,113 --> 00:47:50,607
Alright? Let's go.

806
00:48:08,374 --> 00:48:10,992
[radio wallah
with interference]

807
00:48:13,078 --> 00:48:14,288
Come on!

808
00:48:14,358 --> 00:48:17,227
[piercing sound]

809
00:48:18,868 --> 00:48:19,817
[distant roar]

810
00:48:21,716 --> 00:48:23,756
(male voice over radio
with shrill noise)

811
00:48:23,828 --> 00:48:25,518
--ordered to evacuate
their homes

812
00:48:25,587 --> 00:48:28,685
and take shelter--
[shrill noise]

813
00:48:28,755 --> 00:48:29,802
[click]

814
00:49:09,644 --> 00:49:11,105
Turn the car off!

815
00:49:14,379 --> 00:49:16,353
[growing thunder]

816
00:49:16,427 --> 00:49:17,637
[sizzling]

817
00:49:20,170 --> 00:49:23,879
[sizzling and humming]

818
00:49:25,449 --> 00:49:30,947
[silence]

819
00:49:31,016 --> 00:49:32,260
I think it's gone.

820
00:49:33,448 --> 00:49:34,396
Start the car.

821
00:50:33,726 --> 00:50:34,838
Damn it!

822
00:50:37,469 --> 00:50:38,778
We'll have
to go back.

823
00:50:38,844 --> 00:50:43,546
[loud growing rumble]

824
00:50:44,476 --> 00:50:46,450
[loud cracking]

825
00:50:47,676 --> 00:50:49,017
Get out of
the car now!

826
00:51:12,727 --> 00:51:13,840
Come on! Jump!

827
00:51:16,182 --> 00:51:17,459
[scream]

828
00:51:17,527 --> 00:51:18,704
No!

829
00:51:28,820 --> 00:51:31,853
[distant rumble dies away]

830
00:51:35,764 --> 00:51:36,941
[birds chirping]

831
00:51:41,011 --> 00:51:43,563
[motor starts smoothly]

832
00:52:01,103 --> 00:52:02,313
[gasping]

833
00:52:04,399 --> 00:52:05,380
[scream]

834
00:52:06,830 --> 00:52:07,845
I can't hold on!

835
00:52:07,918 --> 00:52:09,805
Yes, you can!!
Don't let go!!

836
00:52:09,870 --> 00:52:12,903
Help!
Anybody, help!

837
00:52:21,515 --> 00:52:22,344
Grab it!

838
00:52:24,459 --> 00:52:25,408
Come on!!

839
00:52:27,562 --> 00:52:29,766
[groaning]

840
00:52:52,039 --> 00:52:53,860
(James)
We need to
evacuate everyone

841
00:52:53,927 --> 00:52:55,333
from the mini
pole sites.

842
00:52:55,397 --> 00:52:57,917
We just started
rounding up people
for the shelters.

843
00:52:57,989 --> 00:52:59,418
No, you can't
do that.

844
00:52:59,493 --> 00:53:01,980
The plasma charges
building up from
the pole reversal

845
00:53:02,053 --> 00:53:03,514
are escaping
through the
mini poles.

846
00:53:03,588 --> 00:53:05,890
This whole area
is gonna get hit
worse and worse,

847
00:53:05,956 --> 00:53:07,581
as the field fails.

848
00:53:07,652 --> 00:53:09,986
Alright. I'll notify
the soldiers

849
00:53:10,051 --> 00:53:11,131
but communications
have been spotty.

850
00:53:11,204 --> 00:53:12,381
What about
the President?

851
00:53:12,451 --> 00:53:13,661
Will you be able
to contact him?

852
00:53:13,731 --> 00:53:15,258
Yeah, the emergency
hotline is holding up.

853
00:53:15,331 --> 00:53:17,851
Good. I've got
a crazy idea.

854
00:53:17,922 --> 00:53:20,769
I need to
access Storm
Hazard's mainframe.

855
00:53:20,834 --> 00:53:23,135
Oh, follow me.

856
00:53:23,201 --> 00:53:24,248
[phone rings]

857
00:53:26,753 --> 00:53:27,767
Storm Hazards.

858
00:53:27,840 --> 00:53:29,116
Pam, talk to me.

859
00:53:29,185 --> 00:53:30,678
I'm briefing
the President
in a few minutes.

860
00:53:30,752 --> 00:53:33,054
James, the
computer projection--

861
00:53:33,120 --> 00:53:34,461
it's not good.

862
00:53:53,148 --> 00:53:55,057
I need to see
whoever's in charge.

863
00:53:55,132 --> 00:53:56,692
Get that.

864
00:53:56,764 --> 00:53:58,105
Take them in.

865
00:54:01,691 --> 00:54:04,505
Inside this circle
is the most dangerous
place in the west coast.

866
00:54:04,570 --> 00:54:06,871
We're here,
at the epicenter
of the mini pole

867
00:54:06,938 --> 00:54:09,359
creating the
electromagnetic and
seismic disturbances.

868
00:54:09,433 --> 00:54:11,321
We need to move
all of these people

869
00:54:11,385 --> 00:54:13,457
outside the
circle to here.

870
00:54:13,529 --> 00:54:15,154
Where did you get
this information?

871
00:54:15,224 --> 00:54:16,784
My husband,
Dr. James Mayfield.

872
00:54:16,856 --> 00:54:18,034
He's a government
astrophysicist.

873
00:54:18,104 --> 00:54:19,532
He's briefing the
President right now.

874
00:54:19,607 --> 00:54:22,421
I--l--I haven't heard
anything about this.

875
00:54:22,487 --> 00:54:24,974
My orders are to keep
everybody here.

876
00:54:25,047 --> 00:54:27,730
I know, but
I'm telling you
it's not safe here.

877
00:54:27,798 --> 00:54:31,180
Lindenville has become
the magnetic center
of a mini pole.

878
00:54:32,501 --> 00:54:34,541
What is that?
Mini pole?

879
00:54:44,852 --> 00:54:48,364
[motor starts]

880
00:54:56,241 --> 00:54:57,964
No, no, no.
Turn the
power off.

881
00:54:58,033 --> 00:55:00,651
The electricity will
attract the next
EM pulse.

882
00:55:00,721 --> 00:55:02,215
You have to shut
the generator down.

883
00:55:02,289 --> 00:55:04,623
Shut it down?
I don't think so.

884
00:55:04,688 --> 00:55:07,371
You're not
listening to me!
We're in danger here!

885
00:55:07,440 --> 00:55:09,741
Ma'am, federal martial
law has been declared.

886
00:55:09,807 --> 00:55:11,563
I can't just move
hundreds of people

887
00:55:11,631 --> 00:55:13,835
because you show me
some map with a circle
drawn on it.

888
00:55:13,903 --> 00:55:15,790
You know what?
Call General Mayfield.

889
00:55:15,854 --> 00:55:17,261
He'll vouch
for everything
I just said.

890
00:55:24,684 --> 00:55:26,473
(James)
Storm Hazard's lab
just ran this projection.

891
00:55:26,541 --> 00:55:30,980
This is what the magnetic
field normally looks like.

892
00:55:31,051 --> 00:55:32,295
This is what it
looks like now.

893
00:55:32,363 --> 00:55:34,086
Punctured by
mini poles.

894
00:55:36,843 --> 00:55:39,232
This is 12 hours out.

895
00:55:39,306 --> 00:55:42,273
24 hours out,

896
00:55:42,346 --> 00:55:44,200
48 hours out.

897
00:55:44,266 --> 00:55:46,534
Magnetic field
at zero Gauss.

898
00:55:46,600 --> 00:55:48,356
Gentlemen, we
have two days

899
00:55:48,424 --> 00:55:50,977
before our planet loses
its protective shield.

900
00:55:51,048 --> 00:55:54,081
and solar radiation
burns us all to
a crisp.

901
00:56:03,590 --> 00:56:06,459
Anyone here
take issue with Dr.
Mayfield's projections?

902
00:56:06,534 --> 00:56:07,908
No, sir.

903
00:56:07,973 --> 00:56:09,663
No, sir.

904
00:56:11,716 --> 00:56:13,309
Alright, then,

905
00:56:13,380 --> 00:56:16,543
so who's got a
game plan to stop
this pole reversal?

906
00:56:16,611 --> 00:56:18,880
Alright, this is
the way I see it.

907
00:56:18,947 --> 00:56:21,368
What if we detonate
a nuclear explosion

908
00:56:21,443 --> 00:56:22,970
of a magnitude equal
to that with which

909
00:56:23,043 --> 00:56:24,449
the comet
fragment hit Earth

910
00:56:24,515 --> 00:56:26,107
in the
opposing hemisphere

911
00:56:26,178 --> 00:56:28,087
so that it
pushes back
with equal force?

912
00:56:28,162 --> 00:56:29,656
Are you crazy?

913
00:56:29,730 --> 00:56:31,137
How do we know
it wouldn't make
things worse?

914
00:56:31,202 --> 00:56:32,314
What about fallout?

915
00:56:32,385 --> 00:56:34,010
Fallout?

916
00:56:34,081 --> 00:56:37,147
The pole reversal
completes in
48 hours

917
00:56:37,217 --> 00:56:40,118
and then it is
bye-bye planet.

918
00:56:40,192 --> 00:56:42,777
Does anybody else
have a better idea?

919
00:56:47,871 --> 00:56:48,983
That's what
I thought.

920
00:56:49,054 --> 00:56:50,330
That comet
fragment hit us

921
00:56:50,399 --> 00:56:52,253
with the force of
a 100-megaton bomb.

922
00:56:52,318 --> 00:56:53,944
We don't
have a warhead
that powerful.

923
00:56:54,014 --> 00:56:56,533
What's the most
powerful nuke in
the U.S. arsenal?

924
00:56:56,605 --> 00:56:59,867
We have a new 50-megaton
prototype that's at the
nuclear test site.

925
00:56:59,933 --> 00:57:02,583
We can do a
double detonation
to equal a hundred.

926
00:57:05,756 --> 00:57:07,610
[noises over radio]

927
00:57:08,827 --> 00:57:09,940
And?

928
00:57:10,010 --> 00:57:11,417
We can't get through
to the general.

929
00:57:11,482 --> 00:57:12,660
Our communications
are down.

930
00:57:12,731 --> 00:57:14,225
We can't just leave
these people here.

931
00:57:14,298 --> 00:57:16,469
This place is a
ticking time bomb.

932
00:57:16,538 --> 00:57:18,926
I suggest
you find a cot
and you chill.

933
00:57:22,425 --> 00:57:23,635
And?

934
00:57:23,704 --> 00:57:24,914
(soldier)
Not yet, sir.

935
00:57:28,120 --> 00:57:29,068
Zoe!

936
00:57:29,144 --> 00:57:30,453
Hey, when did
you get here?

937
00:57:30,519 --> 00:57:31,948
Just a few
minutes ago.

938
00:57:32,023 --> 00:57:36,812
Excuse me, everybody.
Can I have your
attention please?

939
00:57:36,886 --> 00:57:38,893
Hi, I'm
Cynthia Mayfield,

940
00:57:38,966 --> 00:57:41,387
I'm a science teacher
at Lindenville High.

941
00:57:41,462 --> 00:57:44,211
Many of you know that
my husband, Dr.
James Mayfield

942
00:57:44,277 --> 00:57:46,186
is a
respected astrophysicist.

943
00:57:46,261 --> 00:57:49,228
He's told me
that our town
is the epicenter

944
00:57:49,301 --> 00:57:51,405
of the
electromagnetic and
seismic disturbances

945
00:57:51,476 --> 00:57:53,167
that is
happening on
the west coast

946
00:57:53,236 --> 00:57:56,203
and that it's very
dangerous to stay here.

947
00:57:56,275 --> 00:57:58,642
So we need to move
outside the circle.

948
00:57:58,706 --> 00:58:00,429
The nearest
safe town is
Little Brook.

949
00:58:00,498 --> 00:58:02,440
(soldier)
You want to step
down from there, ma'am?

950
00:58:02,514 --> 00:58:04,401
How come the
soldiers don't
know this?

951
00:58:04,465 --> 00:58:06,058
Because their
communications are down.

952
00:58:06,129 --> 00:58:07,373
They're completely
in the dark.

953
00:58:07,442 --> 00:58:08,783
I'm not gonna ask
you again, ma'am.

954
00:58:08,849 --> 00:58:11,783
Please, listen to me.
We could all die here!

955
00:58:11,856 --> 00:58:13,711
Get her off
of there.

956
00:58:15,023 --> 00:58:16,616
Is it true?

957
00:58:21,134 --> 00:58:24,134
If you open your
mouth about this
to anyone again,

958
00:58:24,207 --> 00:58:27,076
you will
be arrested.
Is that clear?

959
00:58:27,149 --> 00:58:29,637
Yes.

960
00:58:29,710 --> 00:58:32,938
And I don't want
to see that
map again.

961
00:58:33,004 --> 00:58:33,898
Release her.

962
00:58:46,059 --> 00:58:47,302
(general)
James, you'll
be happy to know

963
00:58:47,370 --> 00:58:48,996
that the
bomber is
on its way.

964
00:58:49,067 --> 00:58:52,579
And 250-megaton
warheads will launch
at 16:00 hours.

965
00:59:06,535 --> 00:59:08,258
[phone rings]

966
00:59:08,327 --> 00:59:09,275
Yes?

967
00:59:11,302 --> 00:59:12,927
What do you mean
we lost the plane?

968
00:59:16,294 --> 00:59:17,701
Yes.
Thank you.

969
00:59:20,292 --> 00:59:22,332
An EM pulse took
out the bomber.

970
00:59:22,405 --> 00:59:24,412
The warheads
exploded in midair.

971
00:59:24,484 --> 00:59:26,239
They have to try again.
Send another plane.

972
00:59:26,307 --> 00:59:29,089
James, the skies are
unflyable. We'll
lose them all.

973
00:59:29,155 --> 00:59:31,872
They have to try.
Send 20 planes.
One might get through.

974
00:59:31,939 --> 00:59:33,946
James. James.

975
00:59:34,019 --> 00:59:37,084
You have to think
of something
else. Fast.

976
00:59:37,154 --> 00:59:39,194
There's got to
be another way.

977
00:59:39,266 --> 00:59:40,924
(Cyn)
We've got to
get out of here.

978
00:59:40,994 --> 00:59:44,092
Why would the soldiers
keep us here if it
isn't safe?

979
00:59:44,161 --> 00:59:46,430
Because they
don't know anything.

980
00:59:46,497 --> 00:59:48,885
They're just
following their
last orders.

981
00:59:48,960 --> 00:59:50,334
Communications have
gotten so bad

982
00:59:50,399 --> 00:59:52,406
they can't
even contact
their superiors.

983
00:59:55,871 --> 00:59:57,245
What do you
want to do?

984
00:59:59,902 --> 01:00:03,676
Dr. Mayfield was right
when he said the comet
might hit Earth.

985
01:00:03,741 --> 01:00:05,301
I think we
should go.

986
01:00:09,117 --> 01:00:10,065
We're in.

987
01:00:15,067 --> 01:00:16,082
Come on.

988
01:00:16,156 --> 01:00:17,814
It's right over here.

989
01:00:19,323 --> 01:00:20,784
This one here.

990
01:00:41,143 --> 01:00:43,925
Those poor people,
I feel so bad
leaving them.

991
01:00:43,991 --> 01:00:45,900
You did everything
you could, Cyn.

992
01:00:49,590 --> 01:00:52,938
(James)
Gentlemen, I have a
new plan that might just work.

993
01:00:53,013 --> 01:00:54,704
We're gonna detonate
at the bottom of
the ocean,

994
01:00:54,773 --> 01:00:57,456
the Mariana Trench, the
deepest point in
the Earth's crust.

995
01:00:58,389 --> 01:00:59,730
Dr. Elman?

996
01:00:59,796 --> 01:01:01,487
Yes, the
ocean crust
is thin enough

997
01:01:01,556 --> 01:01:03,727
that the blast
could go right through
to the lithosphere

998
01:01:03,796 --> 01:01:07,951
yes, it could conceivably
push the planet back
into alignment.

999
01:01:08,019 --> 01:01:12,077
The Mariana Trench
is over 36,000 feet,
deep, doctor.

1000
01:01:12,146 --> 01:01:13,706
How do you plan
on getting there?

1001
01:01:15,570 --> 01:01:16,911
A submarine.

1002
01:01:16,977 --> 01:01:18,406
Unfortunately, doctor,

1003
01:01:18,481 --> 01:01:20,750
we don't have any
that are operational.

1004
01:01:20,817 --> 01:01:22,126
What do you mean?

1005
01:01:22,192 --> 01:01:24,395
EM interference
crippled the
onboard computers

1006
01:01:24,463 --> 01:01:26,089
that control the
nuclear reactors.

1007
01:01:26,160 --> 01:01:28,745
Are you telling me
there's not a single
sub out there?

1008
01:01:28,815 --> 01:01:30,221
That's right.

1009
01:01:30,287 --> 01:01:33,450
That's not exactly
true, general.

1010
01:01:33,518 --> 01:01:36,616
The Russians have an old
diesel they still
train on.

1011
01:01:36,686 --> 01:01:38,377
She isn't
pretty but
she's running.

1012
01:01:38,446 --> 01:01:41,445
She's on the west coast
for international training.

1013
01:01:58,602 --> 01:01:59,617
Open that bunker.

1014
01:01:59,690 --> 01:02:00,672
Yes, sir!

1015
01:02:19,623 --> 01:02:27,074
[emergency radio wallah]

1016
01:02:27,141 --> 01:02:29,956
I guess they're still
ordering everyone
to the church.

1017
01:02:30,021 --> 01:02:32,639
[radio interference
with whistle]

1018
01:02:32,709 --> 01:02:33,691
I can hear it.

1019
01:02:35,620 --> 01:02:36,732
Hear what?

1020
01:02:36,803 --> 01:02:38,396
An EM
pulse tone.

1021
01:02:38,468 --> 01:02:39,678
What's an
EM pulse tone?

1022
01:02:39,747 --> 01:02:41,340
Electromagnetic shockwave.

1023
01:02:41,411 --> 01:02:45,119
It's a burst of
electromagnetic energy
coming from mini pole.

1024
01:02:49,505 --> 01:02:51,447
That sub should
be in the harbor
by now.

1025
01:02:52,865 --> 01:02:55,734
[shrill whistle over radio]

1026
01:02:55,808 --> 01:02:57,401
What the heck
is that noise?

1027
01:02:57,472 --> 01:02:59,643
It's a pulse tone.
Cut the engine, Dad.

1028
01:02:59,712 --> 01:03:00,759
Now?

1029
01:03:00,832 --> 01:03:01,977
Yes! Stop
the car,
right now!

1030
01:03:16,253 --> 01:03:17,595
[shrill piercing whistle]

1031
01:03:17,661 --> 01:03:18,970
Ah!

1032
01:03:21,660 --> 01:03:23,122
What was that?

1033
01:03:23,196 --> 01:03:25,716
[shrill whistle]

1034
01:03:25,787 --> 01:03:26,736
[click]

1035
01:03:28,411 --> 01:03:29,359
There it is!

1036
01:03:34,586 --> 01:03:35,960
Oh, my God.

1037
01:03:36,025 --> 01:03:37,716
Turn the car
off, Michael!
Turn it off!

1038
01:03:41,945 --> 01:03:43,351
Everything electric
has to be turned off,

1039
01:03:43,416 --> 01:03:45,555
your cell phones,
mp3 players,
everything.

1040
01:03:45,624 --> 01:03:47,892
Get rid of your
watch, Michael.

1041
01:03:49,592 --> 01:03:51,250
[distant roar]

1042
01:03:55,062 --> 01:03:57,331
I hope those guys
remember to cut
their engine.

1043
01:04:05,684 --> 01:04:07,113
Cut your engine!

1044
01:04:18,706 --> 01:04:22,448
[many screams]

1045
01:04:37,136 --> 01:04:38,630
Cut your engine!!

1046
01:04:38,703 --> 01:04:40,109
Cut your engine!!

1047
01:04:57,964 --> 01:04:59,272
I think it passed.

1048
01:05:00,907 --> 01:05:03,274
Michael, what's wrong?

1049
01:05:03,339 --> 01:05:06,241
Dad? Are
you okay?

1050
01:05:07,722 --> 01:05:08,802
Can you drive?

1051
01:05:08,874 --> 01:05:09,986
Sure.

1052
01:05:15,529 --> 01:05:17,504
James! Check
the engine.

1053
01:05:18,728 --> 01:05:21,313
We've got
no time
to waste.

1054
01:05:31,206 --> 01:05:33,278
Battery and
accelerator are fried.

1055
01:05:38,341 --> 01:05:41,090
Looks like we may
be an hour away from
getting out of the circle.

1056
01:05:41,156 --> 01:05:43,098
We need to get
my father to
a hospital.

1057
01:05:43,172 --> 01:05:44,578
What's wrong?

1058
01:05:44,644 --> 01:05:46,716
He has a pacemaker.
I think the storm
shorted it out.

1059
01:05:48,355 --> 01:05:50,177
Oh, God!

1060
01:06:03,553 --> 01:06:04,796
Here.

1061
01:06:19,806 --> 01:06:21,049
How are
we doing?

1062
01:06:21,117 --> 01:06:22,328
Good. Give
it a try.

1063
01:06:22,398 --> 01:06:23,346
Okay.

1064
01:06:29,468 --> 01:06:31,802
[motor starts]

1065
01:06:54,744 --> 01:07:00,821
[Russian wallah]

1066
01:07:02,326 --> 01:07:03,504
[horn honks]

1067
01:07:22,451 --> 01:07:24,240
It is an honor,
General Mayfield.

1068
01:07:24,307 --> 01:07:25,616
Captain Yolenkov.

1069
01:07:25,683 --> 01:07:27,111
This is
Dr. Mayfield.

1070
01:07:27,186 --> 01:07:28,134
Captain.

1071
01:07:28,210 --> 01:07:29,639
I see
the resemblance.

1072
01:07:29,714 --> 01:07:32,364
There are two
warheads in the
back of that truck.

1073
01:07:32,433 --> 01:07:35,466
[speaks Russian]

1074
01:07:37,488 --> 01:07:41,230
So, we work
together to
save world, no?

1075
01:07:41,296 --> 01:07:45,518
Yes. Dr. Mayfield
will formulate the
detonation sequence.

1076
01:07:45,583 --> 01:07:49,477
My ship, she strong as ox
but she's not so fast,
you know.

1077
01:07:49,551 --> 01:07:52,333
Yes. We know.

1078
01:08:02,700 --> 01:08:05,067
The closest town is
Clarksville. We passed
it a few minutes ago.

1079
01:08:05,132 --> 01:08:06,692
Maybe they
have a hospital.

1080
01:08:06,764 --> 01:08:08,073
No, don't go back.

1081
01:08:08,140 --> 01:08:10,790
I'm okay.
Just get out
of the circle.

1082
01:08:10,859 --> 01:08:13,641
[shrill whistle]

1083
01:08:17,418 --> 01:08:18,792
Oh, no,
not again.

1084
01:08:20,106 --> 01:08:22,920
[shrill whistle]

1085
01:08:22,985 --> 01:08:25,254
[distant roar]

1086
01:08:25,321 --> 01:08:27,622
(general)
They've gotta get
out of here fast.

1087
01:08:38,982 --> 01:08:41,121
(man)
Get out or I'll
blow your head off.

1088
01:08:41,190 --> 01:08:43,556
Okay.
Okay, okay.

1089
01:08:43,621 --> 01:08:46,239
Everyone get out
or I'll kill
all of you!

1090
01:08:46,309 --> 01:08:48,251
Please, my father
is having a
heart attack,

1091
01:08:48,325 --> 01:08:50,146
we have to get
him to a hospital.

1092
01:08:50,213 --> 01:08:53,060
Get out or I'll
put him out of
his misery.

1093
01:08:53,124 --> 01:08:55,938
Take it easy.
We're going.

1094
01:09:01,410 --> 01:09:02,359
Get out.

1095
01:09:17,952 --> 01:09:19,740
[shout]

1096
01:09:23,967 --> 01:09:25,341
[shout]

1097
01:09:25,406 --> 01:09:26,355
Dad!

1098
01:09:35,869 --> 01:09:39,610
[intermittent beeping]

1099
01:09:53,370 --> 01:09:55,759
What are the conditions
in the Mariana Trench?

1100
01:09:55,833 --> 01:09:58,386
Expect seismic
activity like
you've never seen.

1101
01:09:58,457 --> 01:10:00,180
You should
warn your crew

1102
01:10:00,248 --> 01:10:01,709
that the steam vents
will be heating up
the ocean

1103
01:10:01,784 --> 01:10:03,410
causing violent
current shifts.

1104
01:10:03,481 --> 01:10:06,611
Hm. All
this from rock
hitting Earth?

1105
01:10:06,679 --> 01:10:10,290
Technically, the
comet fragment was
made of ice, but yes.

1106
01:10:10,359 --> 01:10:15,922
So tell me, Dr. Mayfield,
you plan to detonate
these bombs at one time

1107
01:10:15,990 --> 01:10:19,372
[sigh]
No. Not exactly.

1108
01:10:19,445 --> 01:10:21,419
In order
to get a
100-megaton explosion,

1109
01:10:21,493 --> 01:10:26,162
I need to formulate a
detonation sequence
just milliseconds apart.

1110
01:10:26,228 --> 01:10:30,700
You know, of course, that
this vessel cannot outrun
such a shockwave.

1111
01:10:34,195 --> 01:10:35,210
We know.

1112
01:10:37,330 --> 01:10:40,363
Your crew, captain.
Do they know?

1113
01:10:40,434 --> 01:10:44,110
They have volunteered
for this mission,

1114
01:10:44,177 --> 01:10:46,762
in order
to save
their families.

1115
01:10:48,752 --> 01:10:50,213
[buzz]

1116
01:10:50,288 --> 01:10:52,143
[beep]

1117
01:10:52,208 --> 01:10:53,768
[thud]

1118
01:10:53,840 --> 01:10:57,135
Outrunning the
shockwave is the
least of our worries.

1119
01:12:02,084 --> 01:12:03,840
It's fried, Shane.

1120
01:12:03,908 --> 01:12:06,144
You know you can't
start a car without
the battery.

1121
01:12:06,211 --> 01:12:07,967
Cars in the old days
didn't have batteries.

1122
01:12:08,035 --> 01:12:09,213
They had
hand cranks.

1123
01:12:09,283 --> 01:12:11,137
Yeah, well,
we don't have
a hand crank,

1124
01:12:11,202 --> 01:12:12,795
and this is
a modern car.

1125
01:12:12,866 --> 01:12:15,484
You don't
need a battery
to drive either.

1126
01:12:15,554 --> 01:12:17,342
All yo need to
do is capture an
electrical charge

1127
01:12:17,409 --> 01:12:19,197
so it'll
help ignite
the spark plugs.

1128
01:12:19,265 --> 01:12:21,654
Where are we
gonna get
that from?

1129
01:12:37,502 --> 01:12:40,120
Ever seen
anything like this?

1130
01:12:40,189 --> 01:12:41,433
No one has.

1131
01:12:41,501 --> 01:12:44,119
We're witnessing
a geological event

1132
01:12:44,189 --> 01:12:46,360
that hasn't happened
on this scale in
millions of years.

1133
01:12:46,429 --> 01:12:49,494
What creates
such hell?

1134
01:12:52,956 --> 01:12:55,410
Massive techtonic movements.

1135
01:12:55,483 --> 01:12:58,298
How will this
affect the mission?

1136
01:12:58,363 --> 01:13:00,697
Well, it makes it
nearly impossible.

1137
01:13:36,180 --> 01:13:38,252
[metal groaning]

1138
01:13:45,043 --> 01:13:46,766
[metal groaning]

1139
01:14:01,104 --> 01:14:02,697
[shouts]

1140
01:14:25,452 --> 01:14:27,786
[ringing]

1141
01:14:27,851 --> 01:14:30,534
[speaks Russian]

1142
01:14:30,603 --> 01:14:32,643
[male voice over radio,
speaks in Russian]

1143
01:14:32,715 --> 01:14:33,794
Dad.

1144
01:14:48,680 --> 01:14:49,694
Dad.

1145
01:14:49,767 --> 01:14:51,076
I'm okay.

1146
01:14:54,375 --> 01:14:57,058
We have
lost one engine.

1147
01:14:57,127 --> 01:14:58,850
Power will
be 50%.

1148
01:15:12,451 --> 01:15:13,433
Hey.

1149
01:15:18,595 --> 01:15:20,896
Can Shane really
do what he says
he's doing?

1150
01:15:22,882 --> 01:15:25,500
All I know is Shane
loves working
with cars.

1151
01:15:25,570 --> 01:15:27,708
He's the
biggest greaser
at our school.

1152
01:15:35,520 --> 01:15:37,211
Better hurry up
with that, Shane.

1153
01:15:59,868 --> 01:16:01,755
100 meters from bottom.

1154
01:16:01,819 --> 01:16:03,281
Almost in position.

1155
01:16:03,355 --> 01:16:04,784
[metal groaning]

1156
01:16:23,512 --> 01:16:24,722
Damn it!

1157
01:16:24,791 --> 01:16:27,027
We cannot stay
at this dept
very long.

1158
01:16:27,095 --> 01:16:29,135
You have a
family, captain?

1159
01:16:29,207 --> 01:16:30,483
Of course.

1160
01:16:30,550 --> 01:16:32,306
So we're gonna stay
here as long as
it takes.

1161
01:16:35,990 --> 01:16:38,128
If we die from
a crushed hull
or a shockwave,

1162
01:16:38,197 --> 01:16:39,691
what difference
does it make?

1163
01:16:39,765 --> 01:16:42,132
If we fail,
the whole
world dies.

1164
01:16:46,612 --> 01:16:48,139
[beeping]

1165
01:16:48,212 --> 01:16:50,350
This is it.

1166
01:16:50,419 --> 01:16:51,848
We're on!

1167
01:16:51,923 --> 01:16:54,889
Okay, I got us
in the timers
on the warheads!

1168
01:16:54,962 --> 01:16:57,711
[speaks Russian]

1169
01:17:01,106 --> 01:17:02,054
Here it comes!

1170
01:17:02,129 --> 01:17:03,438
I'm just
about done.

1171
01:17:03,505 --> 01:17:04,749
I don't think l
should be holding
this anymore.

1172
01:17:04,817 --> 01:17:05,831
Almost there.

1173
01:17:10,224 --> 01:17:11,533
Shane!

1174
01:17:11,600 --> 01:17:12,745
Done!
Antena!

1175
01:17:12,816 --> 01:17:13,743
Tape!

1176
01:17:15,919 --> 01:17:16,867
Come on!

1177
01:17:24,205 --> 01:17:26,147
We need to
move away.

1178
01:17:28,109 --> 01:17:29,123
Shane, come on!

1179
01:17:33,804 --> 01:17:34,916
Let's go!

1180
01:18:16,581 --> 01:18:19,298
I feel happy
to die knowing
it was to--

1181
01:18:19,364 --> 01:18:21,436
save family
on surface.

1182
01:18:23,076 --> 01:18:25,497
But I'm sad
that you must
die with your son.

1183
01:18:27,587 --> 01:18:29,823
Until a few
days ago,

1184
01:18:29,890 --> 01:18:33,054
I hadn't
seen James
in five years.

1185
01:18:35,970 --> 01:18:37,213
So--

1186
01:18:37,281 --> 01:18:39,256
[door creaks]
(James)
We're on.

1187
01:18:52,862 --> 01:18:55,196
It's done, captain.
Fire when ready.

1188
01:18:59,997 --> 01:19:02,299
[alarm sounds]

1189
01:19:17,882 --> 01:19:21,013
It will be impossible
to outrun the shockwave
with one engine,

1190
01:19:21,082 --> 01:19:22,609
but at least
I tried.

1191
01:19:26,521 --> 01:19:28,081
(Shane)
I think it's done.

1192
01:19:30,872 --> 01:19:32,944
We just have to pray
that one static charge

1193
01:19:33,016 --> 01:19:37,074
has been trapped
in the cylinder.

1194
01:19:37,143 --> 01:19:38,485
[motor doesn't start]

1195
01:19:38,551 --> 01:19:39,892
Come on, baby.

1196
01:19:39,958 --> 01:19:41,519
[motor starts]

1197
01:19:43,254 --> 01:19:44,464
Yeah!

1198
01:19:46,390 --> 01:19:47,884
You're a genius!

1199
01:20:04,050 --> 01:20:07,148
We've got the greatest
show on earth here, Dad.

1200
01:20:09,490 --> 01:20:12,304
It's a scientist's
dream, isn't it?

1201
01:20:32,589 --> 01:20:33,571
Captain!

1202
01:20:38,061 --> 01:20:40,516
If you could take
us into that volcano,

1203
01:20:40,588 --> 01:20:43,271
the steam funnel might
propel us out of the
shockwave's path.

1204
01:20:45,132 --> 01:20:48,393
The hull is
not designed
for such temperatures.

1205
01:20:48,459 --> 01:20:51,775
Hm. What have
we got to lose?

1206
01:21:09,704 --> 01:21:11,492
[loud metal groaning]

1207
01:21:17,734 --> 01:21:19,774
Hull temperature
is rising.

1208
01:21:19,846 --> 01:21:22,366
The heat
is expanding
the metal.

1209
01:21:22,438 --> 01:21:24,226
[static]

1210
01:21:40,034 --> 01:21:41,692
Brace yourselves.

1211
01:22:35,801 --> 01:22:39,149
(President)
Thanks to unprecedented
cooperation between nations,

1212
01:22:39,225 --> 01:22:45,301
we have survived the
most catastrophic event to
ever threaten our existence.

1213
01:22:45,367 --> 01:22:48,084
The Earth has been healed.

1214
01:22:48,151 --> 01:22:51,631
The human spirit
has triumphed.

1215
01:22:51,703 --> 01:22:55,761
But we will honor those lost
with our resolve to rebuild,

1216
01:22:55,830 --> 01:22:59,244
and we will rejoice
in what we've
been given.

1217
01:22:59,317 --> 01:23:01,935
A chance for
a new beginning.

1218
01:23:05,556 --> 01:23:07,944
Ten a.m.
Perfect time.

1219
01:23:09,875 --> 01:23:11,730
And finally,

1220
01:23:11,795 --> 01:23:15,439
our fragile planet
owes a huge debt
to Dr. James Mayfield.

1221
01:23:35,119 --> 01:23:36,296
He's here.

1222
01:23:45,293 --> 01:23:46,537
(Shane)
Dad!

1223
01:23:54,700 --> 01:23:56,969
(James)
This is
your grandfather.

1224
01:24:01,700 --> 01:24:03,969
"<u>ThE EnD</u>"

